---
import BaseHead from '../../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import HeaderEn from '../../../components/HeaderEn.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead
    title="Child Custody Lawyer Toronto | CAS · Emergency Motions · International | Miao He"
    description="Child custody and parenting time disputes in Ontario. CAS intervention, emergency motions, international relocation, Hague Convention. Mandarin and English. 647-930-6688."
  />
  <meta name="keywords" content="child custody lawyer Toronto,parenting time Ontario,CAS lawyer GTA,emergency custody motion Ontario,international child relocation lawyer,Hague Convention lawyer Ontario,Chinese family lawyer custody" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.miaohelaw.ca/en/family-law/child-custody" />
  <link rel="alternate" hreflang="zh" href="https://www.miaohelaw.ca/family-law/child-custody" />
  <link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://www.miaohelaw.ca/en/family-law/child-custody" />
  <style>
    *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}body{font-family:Georgia,serif;background:#0F0A04;color:#E8D5B0}a{color:inherit;text-decoration:none}
    .lang-bar{background:#1A1208;text-align:right;padding:.4rem 2rem;font-size:.8rem}.lang-bar a{color:#C8B99A;margin-left:1rem}.lang-bar a.active{color:#D4A853;font-weight:600}
    .page{max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 2rem}
    .breadcrumb{font-size:.78rem;color:#A89070;margin-bottom:2rem}.breadcrumb a{color:#D4A853}
    h1{font-size:2rem;color:#F5E6C8;margin-bottom:.5rem}
    .lead{color:#C8B99A;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:2rem}
    .card{background:#1A1208;border:1px solid #3A3020;border-radius:8px;padding:2rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem}
    .card h2{color:#D4A853;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;letter-spacing:.05em}
    .card p{color:#C8B99A;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:.8rem}
    .card ul{list-style:none;padding:0}.card ul li{color:#C8B99A;font-size:.85rem;padding:.3rem 0 .3rem 1.2rem;position:relative}.card ul li::before{content:"·";position:absolute;left:0;color:#D4A853}
    .faq-item{border-bottom:1px solid #3A3020;padding:1rem 0}.faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .faq-q{color:#F5E6C8;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:.4rem}
    .faq-a{color:#A89070;font-size:.83rem;line-height:1.7}
    .cta{text-align:center;padding:2rem}.cta h2{color:#D4A853;margin-bottom:1rem}
    .btn-primary{display:inline-block;background:#D4A853;color:#1A1208;padding:.75rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;font-weight:700;margin:.5rem}
    .btn-secondary{display:inline-block;border:1px solid #D4A853;color:#D4A853;padding:.75rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;margin:.5rem}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="lang-bar"><a href="/family-law/child-custody">中文</a><a href="/en/family-law/child-custody" class="active">EN</a></div>
  <HeaderEn />
  <div class="page">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/en/">Home</a> › Family Law › Child Custody & Access</div>
    <h1>Child Custody & Access</h1>
    <p class="lead">In Ontario, the focus is on parenting time and decision-making responsibility — always guided by the best interests of the child. We protect your relationship with your children at every stage.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>WHAT WE HANDLE</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Contested custody and parenting time disputes</li>
        <li>Emergency motions — immediate risk to children</li>
        <li>CAS (Children's Aid Society) intervention and response</li>
        <li>International relocation applications</li>
        <li>Hague Convention — international child abduction</li>
        <li>Variation of existing custody orders</li>
        <li>Parenting coordination</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is the difference between decision-making responsibility and parenting time?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Decision-making responsibility (formerly "custody") refers to who makes major decisions about the child's education, health, and religion. Parenting time (formerly "access") refers to the time each parent physically spends with the child. Both can be shared or allocated to one parent.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">CAS has been involved with my family. What should I do?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Contact a lawyer immediately. CAS involvement can have significant consequences for custody proceedings. We have experience responding to CAS investigations and representing parents in protection proceedings.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can I take my children to China without the other parent's consent?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">If there is a court order in place, you must follow it. Taking children out of the country without consent or court approval can constitute child abduction and has serious legal consequences. Always consult a lawyer first.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card cta">
      <h2>Book a Consultation</h2>
      <a href="tel:6479306688" class="btn-primary">📞 647-930-6688</a>
      <a href="mailto:miao@miaohelaw.ca" class="btn-secondary">Email Us</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>
